"""
dnsbench: a completely unnecessary, single-file DNS benchmark cockpit.

It still does exactly what the original script was meant to do: benchmark the
hard-coded homelab DNS servers below. It just now does it with enough ceremony
that it probably deserves a tiny clipboard and a change advisory.

Core safety properties:
  * Benchmark traffic is time-bound by default. Use --continuous to run forever.
  * Every upstream must pass a health check before benchmark traffic is sent.
  * Failed upstreams are quarantined and periodically rechecked with bounded
    health probes instead of being hammered by benchmark retries.
  * Ctrl+C/SIGTERM flips a shared stop event, cancels queued work, and waits a
    bounded amount of time for in-flight DNS calls to unwind.
  * No config file. No sidecar state. No daemon. No permanent DNS spam machine.

Dependencies: requests, dnspython. Everything else is standard library.
"""

